The paper discusses the implementation of a general-purpose societal-scale human-collective problem-solving engine, which involves the use of computer and network technologies. This falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also discusses the use of social-network theory in implementing a representative and expertise system, which falls under the category of Cybersecurity (cs.CY) and Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of collective intelligence in society, which falls under the category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SOC).
